{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Chronicles 11 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:1",
      "text": "And Roboam came to Jerusalem; and he assembled Juda and Benjamin, a hundred and eighty thousand young men fit for war, and he waged war with Israel to recover the kingdom to Roboam.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:2",
      "text": "And the Word of the Lord came to Samaias the man of God, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:3",
      "text": "Speak to Roboam the son of Solomon, and to all Juda and Benjamin, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:4",
      "text": "Thus saith the Lord, Ye shall not go up, and ye shall not war against your brethren: return every one to his home; for this thing is of me. And they hearkened to the word of the Lord, and returned from going against Jeroboam.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:5",
      "text": "And Roboam dwelt in Jerusalem, and he built walled cities in Judea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:6",
      "text": "And he built Bethleem, and Ætan and Thecoe,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:7",
      "text": "and Baethsura, and Sochoth, and Odollam,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:8",
      "text": "and Geth, and Marisa, and Ziph,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:9",
      "text": "and Adorai, and Lachis, and Azeca,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:10",
      "text": "and Saraa, and Ælom, and Chebron, which belong to Juda and Benjamin, walled cities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:11",
      "text": "And he fortified them with walls, and placed in them captains, and stores of provisions, oil and wine,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:12",
      "text": "shields and spears in every several city, and he fortified them very strongly, and he had on his side Juda and Benjamin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:13",
      "text": "And the priests and the Levites who were in all Israel were gathered to him out of all the coasts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:14",
      "text": "For the Levites left the tents of their possession, and went to Juda to Jerusalem, because Jeroboam and his sons had ejected them so that they should not minister to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:15",
      "text": "And he made for himself priests of the high places, and for the idols, and for the vanities, and for the calves which Jeroboam made.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:16",
      "text": "And he cast out from the tribes of Israel those who set their heart to seek the Lord God of Israel: and they came to Jerusalem, to sacrifice to the Lord God of their fathers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:17",
      "text": "And they strengthened the kingdom of Juda; and Juda strengthened Roboam the son of Solomon for three years, for he walked three years in the ways of David and Solomon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:18",
      "text": "And Roboam took to himself for a wife, Moolath daughter of Jerimuth the son of David, and Abigaia daughter of Heliab the son of Jessae.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:19",
      "text": "And she bore him sons; Jeus, and Samoria, and Zaam.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:20",
      "text": "And afterwards he took to himself Maacha the daughter of Abessalom; and she bore him Abia, and Jetthi, and Zeza, and Salemoth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:21",
      "text": "And Roboam loved Maacha the daughter of Abessalom more than all his wives and all his concubines: for he had eighteen wives and sixty concubines; and he begot twenty-eight sons, and sixty daughters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:22",
      "text": "And he made Abia the son of Maacha chief, even a leader among his brethren, for he intended to make him king.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:second-chronicles.11.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 11:23",
      "text": "And he was exalted beyond all his other sons in all the coasts of Juda and Benjamin, and in the strong cities; and he gave them provisions in great abundance: and he desired many wives.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
